            "config": {
              "id": "QUE60287",
              "question": "In his speech introduction, Jacyn decided to warm up the audience by telling a few jokes. He then proceeded to tell two different anecdotes, and ended his introduction with a quotation. As he moved into the body of his speech, his audience didn’t seem to be following him. What mistake did Jacyn make?\n\u003cbr /\u003e",
              "order": "randomized",
              "presenterType": "RadioGroup",
              "presenterConfig": {
                "numberFormat": "none"
              },
              "choices": [
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_1",
                  "content": "He forgot the basic purpose of his introduction— introducing his subject."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_2",
                  "content": "He used multiple methods of introduction; speakers should choose only one method."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_3",
                  "content": "He didn’t attempt to connect with his audience."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_4",
                  "content": "He combined the use of humor with the use of anecdotes, which should never be done."
                }
              ]
            },
